    slug: "what-is-the-holy-quran-how-to-recite-it",
    description: `What is the Holy Quran and How to Recite It is an educational book published by Darussalam under the Education category, designed to introduce readers to the nature, significance, and proper recitation of the Quran — the holy book of Islam. This book serves a dual purpose: first, it explains what the Quran is — its authorship, preservation, structure, themes, and guiding principles — and second, it provides practical instruction on how to recite the Quran correctly, making it an invaluable resource for beginners and those who wish to improve their recitation skills.

The first section of the book establishes the fundamental nature of the Quran. It explains that the Quran is the literal word of Allah, revealed to the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) through the Angel Jibreel (Gabriel) over a period of approximately twenty-three years. The book discusses how the Quran was preserved through both memorization (hifz) and written documentation from the time of its revelation, and how this dual method of preservation has ensured the integrity of the text to the present day. It covers the structure of the Quran, including its division into 114 surahs (chapters), 30 juz (parts), and 60 hizb (sections), along with the significance of Makkan and Madinan revelations.

The book then transitions to the practical aspect of Quranic recitation. It introduces the science of Tajweed — the set of rules governing the proper pronunciation and articulation of Quranic Arabic. The fundamental rules of Tajweed are explained clearly, including the correct pronunciation of Arabic letters (makharij al-huruf), the rules of prolongation (madd), the rules of nasalization (ghunnah), the rules of stopping and starting (waqf and ibtida), and the rules governing the letter "Nun" and "Tanween." Each rule is explained with examples from the Quran, making it easy for readers to understand and apply them.

The book also covers the etiquette (adab) of reciting the Quran, including the recommended conditions for recitation, the importance of ritual purity, the proper posture and attitude during recitation, and the reward associated with reciting and reflecting upon the Quran. It provides guidance for those who are learning to read Quranic Arabic for the first time, as well as tips for those who already read but wish to improve the quality of their recitation.

What is the Holy Quran and How to Recite It is an excellent starting point for new Muslims, children beginning their Quran education, adults who never received formal Quran instruction, and anyone who wants to reconnect with the book of Allah through improved recitation. The book's practical approach, combined with its clear explanations and examples, makes it a valuable educational tool for homes, schools, and Quran learning centers.`,
